      "id": "I_kwDOLfzqsM6vZmZb",
      "title": "Mention specific section when referencing RFC 8017",
      "url": "https://github.com/NeilMadden/jose-deprecate-none-rsa1_5/issues/1",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "NeilMadden",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "",
      "createdAt": "2025-03-24T10:12:38Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:23Z",
      "closedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:23Z",
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "NeilMadden",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "From review by Yaron Sheffer:\n> When first referencing RFC 8017, please include the exact section (7.2, as far as I can tell), because there's a lot of stuff there that's still secure.",
          "createdAt": "2025-03-24T10:13:15Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-03-24T10:13:15Z"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 2,
      "id": "I_kwDOLfzqsM6vZpGH",
      "title": "Clarify that \"none\" is JWS and \"RSA1_5\" is JWE",
      "url": "https://github.com/NeilMadden/jose-deprecate-none-rsa1_5/issues/2",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "NeilMadden",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Yaron Sheffer's review:\n\n> And to my first point about \"alg\" confusion, Sec. 4.2 defines RSA1_5 only for \"encrypting a JWE CEK\" while your draft in Sec. 1.3 says that both \"none\" and \"RSA1_5\" are deprecated for both JWE and JWS.\n",
      "createdAt": "2025-03-24T10:16:42Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:23Z",
      "closedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:23Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 3,
      "id": "I_kwDOLfzqsM6vZrDY",
      "title": "Strengthen guidance in 1.3 from SHOULD to MUST",
      "url": "https://github.com/NeilMadden/jose-deprecate-none-rsa1_5/issues/3",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "NeilMadden",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Yaron Sheffer's review:\n\n> I think the core sentence of this draft is \"Application developers SHOULD disable support for these algorithms by default.\" And IMO it only has a chance of being effective if you change it to a MUST.\n",
      "createdAt": "2025-03-24T10:19:36Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:24Z",
      "closedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:24Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 4,
      "id": "I_kwDOLfzqsM6vZwY8",
      "title": "Add references for security goals",
      "url": "https://github.com/NeilMadden/jose-deprecate-none-rsa1_5/issues/4",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "NeilMadden",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Yaron Sheffer's review:\n\n> \"standard security goal of authenticated encryption with associated data (AEAD)\" - can you provide a reference? Otherwise this is too informal.\n",
      "createdAt": "2025-03-24T10:27:20Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:24Z",
      "closedAt": "2025-03-24T13:38:24Z",
      "comments": []
